    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING PROTECTION AND DIAGNOSTIC SYSTEM (APAds&#8482;) DESCRIPTION, OPERATION, TROUBLESHOOTING,
        REMOVE, INSTALL, AND ELECTRICAL CIRCUIT DIAGRAMS MAINTENANCE MANUAL - TROUBLESHOOTING - APADS DIAGNOSTIC FAULT
        CODES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>APADS DIAGNOSTIC FAULT CODES</title>
        <para>Communication of diagnostic information is provided by a blinking LEDs (Light Emitting Diode) built into
            the module. When a fault occurs, the corresponding fault code is stored in nonvolatile memory. The module
            always broadcasts the appropriate blink code until it is cleared.
        </para>
        <para>Since only one fault code can be displayed at a time, the fault code of highest priority always takes
            precedence. The fault code table displays the order of priority, name, description, and number of blinks
            associated with each fault. Only the highest priority fault is held in memory. Once the fault is cleared, a
            new fault must occur to initiate a new fault code. A "blink" is approximately 1/4 second in duration. Once
            the number of blinks have been broadcast, there is a delay time of two seconds before the fault code is
            repeated.
        </para>
        <para>The fault code is cleared by two methods:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>The fault code is usually cleared by cycling the ignition switch (one second ON, one second OFF)
                    for four consecutive cycles.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Self clearing based on the persistence of the fault. If a fault condition occurs once and does not
                    repeat, the fault code is held for an extended period of time and then cleared. If the fault is
                    repetitive, it will always be retained in memory until the problem is rectified.
                </para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
